    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train - Installation
        - Valve Covers
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="1">
        <title>Valve Covers</title>
        <figure id="e300505" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign08/N08002.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Valve cover mounting bolts - right</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve cover stud bolt assembly (3)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve cover bolt assembly (6)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not use air tools to install valve covers.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install valve cover gasket and right valve cover onto right rocker arm carrier.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten six valve cover bolts and three valve cover stud bolts to
                <hotlnk document="eges390_292.xml" xrefid="E30005B">special torque
                    <xref refid="E30005B"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install valve cover gasket and left valve cover onto left rocker arm carrier.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten seven valve cover bolts and two valve cover stud bolts to special torque.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If removed, install lifting eyes on the rear of each rocker arm carrier and one on the left
                front carrier. Tighten bolts to special torque.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
